<HL>
   Business Brief -- Armstrong World Industries Inc.:
   Company Buys About 75%
   Of Stake Sold by Belzbergs
</HL>
<DATE>
06/01/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   ACK
</CO>
<IN>
BUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK)
</IN>
<LP>
   Armstrong World Industries Inc. disclosed that it bought
about three-fourths of the 11.7% Armstrong stake sold
Wednesday by the Belzberg family of Canada.
   The Belzbergs, who owned 4.8 million shares in Armstrong
through various affiliates, sold their entire block of shares
to Goldman, Sachs &amp; Co. late Wednesday at $35.75 a share,
about $1.625 a share below the prevailing market price.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Lancaster, Pa.-based Armstrong said it purchased about 3.7
million shares through Goldman. The company added that
Goldman indicated "a broad cross-section of buyers" were
interested in purchasing the other 1.1 million shares.
</TEXT>
